args: Vendra! Is that really you? I never\nwould have thought to see you here!
It's been a while, Zace. I heard you were\nstaying in this castle, so I came to visit.
Is this an acquaintance of yours, Zace?
Ah, you are {player_name}, yes?\nI am Vendra, an old friend of Zace's.\nWe were quite close in our youth.
Well, any friend of Zace is welcome here.
Rumor has it you became a merchant.
I did. And while I don't mean to boast,\nI've done rather well for myself.
I'm glad to hear of your success.
Yes, well, my business may be booming,\nbut I wish I could say the same for my\nbody. I'm quite out of shape these days!
Which is one reason I'm here. I was\nrecalling our youth, and thought we\nmight go hunting together again.
He came all this way, so how about it?
Would you care to join us, Your Highness?\nIt should be quite enjoyable.
Aha ha ha! What a haul!\nThe game is plentiful today.
What do you make of that, Zace?\nLooks like I'm not quite so rusty after all.
The hunters of the Azm Tribe sure do live\nup to their reputation. Although...
Vendra, don't you think this is a bit much?\nWe'll never be able to eat all these\nanimals.
Oh, it's fine. We'll just toss out whatever\nwe don't finish.
The purpose of hunting is to live!\nThrowing away perfectly good game is\nno different than throwing away a life!
How can you think such things and still\ncall yourself an Azm?!
I'm no longer with the Azm!\nI don't have to be bound by those rules!
Be that as it may, I'll not stand here and\npermit you to commit such a careless\nwaste of life!
What kind of high and mighty nonsense\nhas gotten into that head of yours?!
Both of you, calm down! There's no need\nto be at one another's throats over this!
In fact, I've got an idea: Let's go back to\nthe castle and share our catch with\neveryone.
...I'm sorry for what happened, Zace.\nI didn't mean for us to fight.
I apologize for becoming heated myself.
I know you've loved bones since we were\nlittle, so I brought you something.
These...these are the bones of a jonabird.
And what beautiful bones they are!\nSee how the grand wings affix themselves\nto such a small frame!
A sturdy femur, as well as a long radius\nand ulna that lose none of their beauty\neven within the heteromorphic structure.
A bird so rare it's legendary...\nI never dreamed I'd see a complete\nspecimen with my own eyes!
I'm delighted that you like it. Looks like all\nthe coin I spent in order to catch it was\nwell spent.
What...did you say? You captured the bird\nthese bones came from?
Take them and go! I have absolutely\nno need for bones like these!
What're you on about?! I brought them\nbecause I thought you'd ENJOY them!
You think I'd be happy that you murdered\na living creature?! I'll say this once more:\nTake them with you and GO!
You'd spit on a man's kindness like this?\nPah! Consider our friendship over!
...You okay, Zace? That was some fight.
I'm sorry you had to see me like that,\n{player_name}.
You haven't done anything to apologize for.\nBut he was an old friend you hadn't seen\nin a long time, right?
Bones are wonderful, but they are still\nthe remnants of living things.
In order to collect bones, living creatures\nmust die. ...Sometimes I forget that.
That is why I must admonish myself.
Yes. I don't want anything to die for my\nown pleasure.
